getDataAfter(bytes32,uint256).details: Retrieves the next value for the queryId after the specified timestamp

params._queryId: is the queryId to look up the value for
params._timestamp: after which to search for next value

getIndexForDataAfter(bytes32,uint256).details: Retrieves next array index of data after the specified timestamp for the queryId

params._queryId: is the queryId to look up the index for
params._timestamp: is the timestamp after which to search for the next index

returns._index: the next index found after the specified timestamp

getIndexForDataBefore(bytes32,uint256).details: Retrieves latest array index of data before the specified timestamp for the queryId

params._queryId: is the queryId to look up the index for
params._timestamp: is the timestamp before which to search for the latest index

returns._index: the latest index found before the specified timestamp

getMultipleValuesBefore(bytes32,uint256,.details: Retrieves multiple uint256 values before the specified timestamp

params._maxAge: the maximum number of seconds before the _timestamp to search for values
params._maxCount: the maximum number of values to return
params._queryId: the unique id of the data query
params._timestamp: the timestamp before which to search for values

returns._timestamps: the timestamps of the values retrieved
returns._values: the values retrieved, ordered from oldest to newest

getNewValueCountbyQueryId(bytes32).details: Counts the number of values that have been submitted for the queryId

returns._0: uint256 count of the number of values received for the queryId

getReporterByTimestamp(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns the address of the reporter who submitted a value for a data ID at a specific time

params._queryId: is ID of the specific data feed
params._timestamp: is the timestamp to find a corresponding reporter for

returns._0: address of the reporter who reported the value for the data ID at the given timestamp

getTimestampbyQueryIdandIndex(bytes32,ui.details: Gets the timestamp for the value based on their index

params._index: is the value index to look up
params._queryId: is the id to look up

isInDispute(bytes32,uint256).details: Determines whether a value with a given queryId and timestamp has been disputed

params._queryId: is the value id to look up
params._timestamp: is the timestamp of the value to look up

returns._0: bool true if queryId/timestamp is under dispute

retrieveData(bytes32,uint256).details: Retrieve value from oracle based on queryId/timestamp
